'''Robert Ward''' was an [[England|English]] scholar, a fellow of [[King's College, Cambridge]] and [[prebendary]] of [[Chichester Cathedral]]. He served in the "Second Cambridge Company" charged by [[James I of England]] with translating the [[Apocrypha]] for the [[King James Version of the Bible]].

==References==
* Nicolson, Adam. (2003) ''God's Secretaries: The Making of the King James Bible.'' New York: HarperCollins ISBN 0-06-095975-4

